headlines.description: — Jalen Green had 26 points and 11 rebounds, and the Houston Rockets beat the Cleveland Cavaliers 117-103 on Saturday for their fifth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Green scores 26 points as Rockets beat Cavaliers 117-103 for their fifth straight victory

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam had 28 points and 11 rebounds, Aaron Nesmith scored 16 points and the Indiana Pacers beat the Brooklyn Nets 121-100 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pacers roll after halftime, beat the Nets 121-100

headlines.description: — Tyrese Maxey shook off a bloody nose caused by Brandon Miller's flagrant foul to score 30 points, Kelly Oubre Jr. chipped in 22 and the Phladelphia 76ers withstood a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Maxey shakes off bloody nose from flagrant foul, leads 76ers over Hornets, 109-98

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Ayo Dosunmu scored a career-high 34 points, Nikola Vucevic added 29 points and 13 rebounds, and the Chicago Bulls pounded the Washington Wizards 127-98 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ayo Dosunmu scores career-high 34 as Bulls pound Wizards 127-98

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Chet Holmgren had 22 points and 11 rebounds, Jalen Williams added 23 points and six assists and Oklahoma City held off the Memphis Grizzlies 118-112 on Saturday night to claim a share of first place in the Western Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thunder beat Grizzlies 118-112, move into a tie with Denver atop the Western Conference standings

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry belatedly celebrated his birthday by returning to the Golden State lineup and leading the Warriors to a much-needed victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry scores 31 in return as Warriors defeat Lakers 128-121 despite 40 points from James

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 31 points despite a twisted ankle, Mike Conley added a season-high 25 points in his return to Utah and the Minnesota Timberwolves topped the struggling Jazz 119-100 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards scores 31 and Conley tallies 25 in his return to Utah to help Timberwolves top Jazz

events.name: New York Knicks at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — Jalen Brunson scored 42 points, becoming the fourth player in franchise history with 40 or more in consecutive games, and the New York Knicks beat the Sacramento Kings 98-91 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brunson becomes fourth Knicks player with consecutive 40-point games, leads New York past Kings
